name: Benjamin Franks
text: Good prices and great location. It has been in Dubuque for a long time. One of the last remaining original restaurants on JFK. Parking lot is very comfortable to park in. Plenty of seating for dine in.

name: Arlene Lee
text: I was in this location Saturday at a very busy time & was very impressed with the efficient manner in which the employees worked.  I had a similar experience one other time I was at this location.  Both times a young man carried my order â€¦More

name: Terry Choi
text: Great pizza done right. Convenient location. Great staff.

name: Rainbow Unicorn
text: I called to ask if they delivered doughnuts and they asked if this was a joke so I told them no I really love doughnuts. They then said to piss off and hung up. Morral of the story? They are not the nicest people. I have them 5 stars because I really love pizza.

name: Samuel S
text: Its a great deal for lunch buffet for the price. I think the place could use some renovations, but the staff was nice and good pizza.

name: Mike Konzen
text: Great lunch buffet. Good price friendly staff

name: Sharon Butler
text: Good but wish the $4.99 coupon work for more than one person very pricey

name: Monty Alexander
text: They hire hard workers with respect and they actually care and it shows. Nice job.

name: Chris Hanson
text: The pizza is very greasy and doesnt taste all that great

name: Sheena Abbitt
text: Horrible...Horrible...Horrible!! Ordered our food and forgot a pizza!! Waited another 30 minutes for that pizza. Waitress never checked on us...need more staff hired ASAP. Shouldn't have just one waitress on a Saturday night!!

name: The 90'S Dude
text: tables r old they wobble floors need a good scrubing needs updating chairs don't all match lights don't all match run out of food and not tell u till u order it serveices sucks takes to long for food and drinks when there is not much people here food not that good

name: Matthew Koch
text: Took over an hour and a half for one pizza and it was disgusting, and the bathrooms were very unsanitary!
